COMPUTER PROFILES
Yelp is an example of a company that uses a special software to detect fake reviews. Review sites are getting more and more savvy to how shady companies are generating manufactured reviews for their clients. For instance, many review websites will now pick up on someone who reviews a pizza shop in New York City at 1:00pm, and then reviews a deli in Los Angeles at 3:00pm. It is obvious that this person was not at both restaurants on the same day. It is also suspicious when a company that may get a few reviews during a month suddenly gets fifty reviews on one day. And, reviews that do not appear to be naturally written are generally flagged as well. Most of this shady behavior is generated using fake profiles and/or computer-generated reviews
